oop.library/--class description--           oop.library/--class description--

  The oop.library contains only one class called RootClass. The methods
  and attributes for this class will be described here.

    METHODS

  OOPRCM_NEW_OBJECT (APTR MemoryPool, APTR *UserObject, struct TagItem *AttrList)
    This method is used to allow a class to create it's own data structure for
    an object. The pointer to this object should be returned in UserObject
    (Example: *UserObject = MyOwnPrivateData). The MemoryPool is a standard
    amiga os memorypool, allocated with only the MEMF_ANY flag. The AttrList
    is a taglist containing the initialisation values for the attributes.
    The method can be viewed as the C++ constructor.

  OOPRCM_DELETE_OBJECT (APTR MemoryPool)
    When an object is deleted, this method is called to allow the class to
    free any private data. The method can be viewed as the C++ destructor.

  OOPRCM_GET_ATTRIBUTES (struct TagItem *AttrList)
    Used to get attribute values. The values will be written in the taglist's
    data fields. Note that the implementing class itself should replace all
    processed tags by TAG_IGNORE and propagate the method upwards if
    necessary, by returning OOPMCR_METHOD_PROPAGATE.

  OOPRCM_SET_ATTRIBUTES (struct TagItem *AttrList)
    Used to set attribute values. Note that the implementing class itself
    should replace all processed tags by TAG_IGNORE and propagate the method
    upwards if necessary, by returning OOPMCR_METHOD_PROPAGATE.


    ATTRIBUTES

  OOPRCA_VERSION - version number of the class.
  OOPRCA_REVISION - revision number of the class.
  OOPRCA_INFO - a general description of the class.
  OOPRCA_AUTHOR - the name of the author of the class.

oop.library/OOP_AddClass                             oop.library/OOP_AddClass

    NAME
  OOP_AddClass -- add a class to the public classlist

    SYNOPSIS
  error = OOP_AddClass(class, name)
  D0                   A0     A1

  LONG OOP_AddClass(APTR, STRPTR);

    FUNCTION
  This function will add a class to the public classlist. If the class
  is already present on the list, this function returns with an
  errorcode.

    INPUTS
  class -- the class that should be added to the list.
  name -- the name under which the class should be made public.

    RESULT
  This function will return OOPACR_OK if the class was added to the list,
  or an errorcode defined in oop.h.

    SEE ALSO
  OOP_RemClass(), oop.h

oop.library/OOP_AddMethod                           oop.library/OOP_AddMethod

    NAME
  OOP_AddMethod -- add a method to a class

    SYNOPSIS
  error = OOP_AddMethod(class, methodID, hook)
  D0                    A0     D0        A1

  LONG OOP_AddMethod(APTR, ULONG, struct Hook *);

    FUNCTION
  A method will be added to a class, if the method did not exist already.
  This function assumes that the given hook is valid. Patching an existing
  method can be done by removing the old method first and then adding the
  new method with the same methodID.

    INPUTS
  class -- the class to which the method should be added.
  methodID -- the unique identification for the method.
  hook -- a completely initialized hook structure. If the h_Data field
          contains anything but NULL, this value will be put in a6. This
          was done to overcome some problems with calling libcode (which
          expect the libbase in a6) through callback hooks (which will
          have the library that contains the callback function in a6).

    RESULT
  OOPAMR_OK, if all went ok. An errorcode defined in oop.h if something
  wasn't right.

    SEE ALSO
  OOP_RemMethod(), oop.h, utility/hooks.h

oop.library/OOP_AddSuperClass                   oop.library/OOP_AddSuperClass

    NAME
  OOP_AddSuperClass -- add a superclass to a class

    SYNOPSIS
  error = OOP_AddSuperClass(class, superClass)
  D0                        A0     A1

  LONG OOP_AddSuperClass(APTR, APTR);

    FUNCTION
  This function will add a superclass to a class. This superclass will then
  be used to provide inheritance for it's subclasses. If a superclass is
  added to a class that already has objects of itself, the needed superclass
  objects are automaticaly added to those objects. Note that the added
  superclass objects will be initialized to their default values.

    INPUTS
  class -- class to add the superclass to.
  superClass -- a class that will provide it's functionality to the specified
                class through inheritance.

    RESULT
  OOPASCR_OK if the adding was successful, an errorcode otherwise.

    SEE ALSO
  OOP_RemSuperClass(), oop.h

oop.library/OOP_DeleteObject                     oop.library/OOP_DeleteObject

    NAME
  OOP_DeleteObject -- deletes an object

    SYNOPSIS
  error = OOP_DeleteObject(object)
  D0                       A0

  LONG OOP_DeleteObject(APTR);

    FUNCTION
  This function will delete an object and all it's superclass objects. Note
  that this function will fail if the given object is a class that has
  objects or if the class is added to the public classlist. If the object
  is a class, all of the classes' methods will also be removed.

    INPUTS
  object -- the object to delete.

    RESULT
  OOPDOR_OK, if successful, an errorcode otherwise.

    SEE ALSO
  OOP_NewObject(), oop.h

oop.library/OOP_DoMethod                             oop.library/OOP_DoMethod

    NAME
  OOP_DoMethod -- perform a method upon an object

    SYNOPSIS
  error = OOP_DoMethod(object, methodID, argList)
  D0                   A0      D0        A1

  LONG OOP_DoMethod(APTR, ULONG, ULONG *);

    FUNCTION
  This function will perform a method upon an object.

    INPUTS
  object -- the object to perform the method upon.
  methodID -- the method that should be performed.
  argList -- an array of ULONG's containing the arguments needed for the
             method. Look at the method description, to see what should
             be in this array.

    RESULT
  OOPMCR_METHOD_ACCEPTED, OOPMCR_METHOD_REJECTED, or an errorcode.

    SEE ALSO
  OOP_DoPropagatedMethod(), OOP_DoSuperMethod(), oop.h

oop.library/OOP_DoPropagatedMethod         oop.library/OOP_DoPropagatedMethod

    NAME
  OOP_DoPropagatedMethod -- perform a method upon an object

    SYNOPSIS
  error - OOP_DoPropagatedMethod(object, methodID, argList)
  D0                             A0      D0        A1

  LONG OOP_DoPropagatedMethod(APTR, ULONG, ULONG *);

    FUNCTION
  This function will perform a method upon an object and all it's superclass
  objects. The method will start at the top of the superclass tree and it
  will be propagated until all superclass objects and the object itself have
  performed the requested method.

    INPUTS
  object -- the object to perform the method upon.
  methodID -- the method that should be performed.
  argList -- an array of ULONG's containing the arguments needed for the
             method. Look at the method description, to see what should
             be in this array.

    RESULT
  OOPMCR_METHOD_ACCEPTED, OOPMCR_METHOD_REJECTED, or an errorcode.

    SEE ALSO
  OOP_DoMethod(), OOP_DoSuperMethod(), oop.h

oop.library/OOP_DoSuperMethod                   oop.library/OOP_DoSuperMethod

    NAME
  OOP_DoSuperMethod -- performs a method upon the superclass objects of the
                       given object.

    SYNOPSIS
  error = OOP_DoSuperMethod(object, methodID, argList)
  D0                        A0      D0        A1

    FUNCTION
  This method will perform the requested method upon the superclass objects
  of the given object. This is needed when a superclass method is redefined
  in the object's class and the original superclass method needs to be
  executed.

    INPUTS
  object -- the object to perform the method upon.
  methodID -- the method that should be performed.
  argList -- an array of ULONG's containing the arguments needed for the
             method. Look at the method description, to see what should
             be in this array.

    RESULT
  OOPMCR_METHOD_ACCEPTED, OOPMCR_METHOD_REJECTED, or an errorcode.

    SEE ALSO
  OOP_DoMethod(), OOP_DoPropagatedMethod(), oop.h

oop.library/OOP_FindClass                           oop.library/OOP_FindClass

    NAME
  OOP_FindClass -- find a class in the public classlist.

    SYNOPSIS
  class = OOP_FindClass(name)
  D0                    A0

  APTR OOP_FindClass(STRPTR);

    FUNCTION
  This function will return a pointer to the requested class, this pointer
  is needed for all other functions in the library.

    INPUTS
  name -- the name of the class.

    RESULT
  NULL, if the class couldn't be found, or if an error occured. A pointer to
  the requested class if successful.

    SEE ALSO

oop.library/OOP_NewObject                           oop.library/OOP_NewObject

    NAME
  OOP_NewObject -- create a new instantiation of a class

    SYNOPSIS
  object = OOP_NewObject(class, argList)
  D0                     A0     A1

  APTR OOP_NewObject(APTR, struct TagItem *);

    FUNCTION
  This will create a new object and all it's superclass objects as necessary.
  The objects will initialized with the values the are stored in the argList.

    INPUTS
  class - class of which an object should be created.
  argList - a taglist of attributes, with which the newly created objects
            should be initialized.

    RESULT
  a pointer to the created object, if all went ok. NULL if an error occured.

    SEE ALSO
  OOP_DeleteObject(), utility/tagitem.h

